{
  "stem": "10829.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, this-- this kind of life lasted for-- for-- well, it seems to be like a lifetime.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- but it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't think it was more than about six months to a year.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was still in '41.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in '35, so we're talking about six, seven years old.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] during the daily life, if you weren't killed, every so often, the the Germans or the Ukraines or the villagers would come in, and if they didn't like you, or they liked you or whatever, or they just felt nasty that day, or drunk-- you would find in those days the-- the Polacks, the villagers, most of them were-- were drunkards.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Most of them were hoodlums.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not an educated man, but to the history that I know of and overhearing and that, most of the villagers down there were-- were-- they were goyim.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't have the education.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So it was all religious things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And what they were taught is strictly taught from-- from-- of hatred, and the Jews were the rich.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Jews, we had the education, and-- and they were taught that we-- we were their enemy from life on, maybe because of Christ, or-- And those were all religious people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You're talking about Catholic Polacks, which were the Catholic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you're talking the Ukraines.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So you had the Eastern and you had Roman Catholics.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So part of-- part of their enemy was the Jew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you had when-- in the fields, and I remember when we walked by, you had gazebos, whatever you call, you had the statue of Jesus Christ all over, and you had them-- [INAUDIBLE] and we looked at them as the enemy.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
